1
00:00:01,850 --> 00:00:03,810
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,810 --> 00:00:06,950
Oh, no! Jellal's been brought back to life!

3
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:07,730
But...

4
00:00:07,730 --> 00:00:10,850
If you don't bring Wendy back 
soon, Erza's in real trouble!

5
00:00:10,850 --> 00:00:12,410
Fast is good!

6
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:14,950
Natsu, I'll hold him here!

7
00:00:14,950 --> 00:00:16,940
You hurry to Erza's side!

8
00:00:16,940 --> 00:00:17,850
Fast is...

9
00:00:17,850 --> 00:00:19,600
I heard ya the first time!

10
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:28,670
If it's love and dreams and you it'll become magical.

11
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:35,840
Now, let's cast a smile spell!

12
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:48,770
I kind of admired this powerful world,

13
00:00:48,770 --> 00:00:53,190
chock-full of problems.

14
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:59,970
Frozen time has started to move again

15
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:05,580
ever since I met you.

16
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:11,000
Why were we born? Why do we live?

17
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,840
I don't need any complicated answers.

18
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:22,780
Laugh! Cry! Be honest with yourself.

19
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:27,560
Simple feelings are the most important.

20
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:35,900
You can change those tears shed on sad nights into strength.

21
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:42,530
Now, let's cast a smile spell!

22
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:55,150
The Worth Woodsea.

23
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:03,950
Deep inside it, there is a single man.

24
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:15,730
You okay, Happy?

25
00:02:15,730 --> 00:02:17,800
Natsu, where are we?

26
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,800
Don't talk. Just rest there a little while.

27
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,660
But, Jellal...

28
00:02:22,660 --> 00:02:23,600
Jellal...

29
00:02:23,950 --> 00:02:27,830
That bastard! Why the hell is <i>he</i> here?

30
00:02:29,110 --> 00:02:30,200
Natsu-kun!

31
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:34,230
What's wrong, Natsu?

32
00:02:34,730 --> 00:02:35,960
Can you hear me?

33
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:38,040
That voice...

34
00:02:41,710 --> 00:02:43,540
Dead Grand Prix!

35
00:02:47,670 --> 00:02:50,030
Natsu-kun, can you hear me?

36
00:02:50,030 --> 00:02:51,720
Who are you?

37
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:57,500
It's me. Hibiki, from Blue Pegasus.

38
00:02:57,950 --> 00:03:01,700
Thank goodness. I was getting worried 
after not being able to contact anyone.

39
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,380
Oh! Where are you?

40
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:08,010
Not so loud. One of the 
enemy has very good hearing.

41
00:03:08,330 --> 00:03:11,060
It's possible he could 
intercept our conversation.

42
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:14,840
That's why I'm speaking 
directly into your mind.

43
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,860
So, how are Wendy-chan and the cat?

44
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:21,740
They're here, although she's unconscious.

45
00:03:21,990 --> 00:03:23,870
Happy's awake, though.

46
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,840
I see. Thank goodness.

47
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,220
Great job.

48
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:31,510
I'm going to upload an app directly 
into your head that'll guide you here.

49
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:35,650
The cat seems to have used too much magic 
and taken too much damage for me to connect...

50
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:38,290
Anyway, hurry back here.

51
00:03:38,290 --> 00:03:41,000
Sure. What about an apple?

52
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,360
I don't get you.

53
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:48,750
Why have you been talking to yourself?

54
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:51,630
I don't really get it, but 
I have an apple in my head!

55
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:55,460
Wait! I totally know how 
to get to where Erza is!

56
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:57,410
It's like I've known all along!

57
00:03:57,410 --> 00:04:00,500
I don't have any apples in my head!

58
00:04:01,340 --> 00:04:02,620
Hurry, Natsu-kun.

59
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:08,880
You have to hurry... There's no time.

60
00:04:09,620 --> 00:04:13,740
So, how did you tell Natsu where we are?

61
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:18,120
My magic, Archive, can compress information.

62
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:24,080
By compressing it, people can transfer 
information between each other more quickly.

63
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:27,030
I've never heard of magic like that before.

64
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:32,770
Using magic to convert information into 
data is a recent concept, you see.

65
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,750
I see.

66
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:41,150
Anyway, thank goodness Wendy is safe.

67
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:44,290
Just wait a little longer, Erza.

68
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,810
You can do it!

69
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:51,890
I'll protect you until Natsu 
comes back. I promise!

70
00:04:57,160 --> 00:05:00,650
Hey! What are you smiling 
about at a time like this?

71
00:05:00,650 --> 00:05:04,600
Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to offend you.

72
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:14,250
Around that time...

73
00:05:14,910 --> 00:05:22,080
Gray is confronting one of 
Oracion Seis, codenamed Racer.

74
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:26,310
You've stopped me twice now.

75
00:05:26,730 --> 00:05:29,750
At this rate, my name will mean dirt.

76
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:31,690
Oh, is that so?

77
00:05:31,690 --> 00:05:36,430
If I felt like it, it wouldn't be any 
trouble to catch up with those brats.

78
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:37,480
When did you...

79
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:40,840
But I won't feel satisfied 
until you're history.

80
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,070
I'll have plenty of time 
to catch up afterwards.

81
00:05:43,070 --> 00:05:44,910
I don't think so, buddy!

82
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,470
Too slow!

83
00:05:51,470 --> 00:05:53,240
Slow, slow, slow!

84
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:55,860
Damn it! I can't follow him with my eyes!

85
00:05:57,360 --> 00:06:01,250
Even if you used up your magic 
power making this ice wall,

86
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:03,800
I hope you don't expect me to go easy on you.

87
00:06:04,210 --> 00:06:06,120
Say that again, jerk!

88
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,920
Come at me as fast as you can!

89
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,380
Dead Grand Prix!

90
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:12,760
Start your engines!

91
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:22,980
What kind of noise is this?

92
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:29,240
Magic motorcycles!

93
00:06:32,410 --> 00:06:36,870
What the hell? A ton of magic motorcycles?

94
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,250
The motor show from hell!

95
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:43,170
Dance.

96
00:06:43,910 --> 00:06:45,980
You expect me to ride one of these things?!

97
00:06:45,980 --> 00:06:49,500
These are machines made 
to match my own speed.

98
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:52,020
Slowpokes can't handle 'em.

99
00:06:53,010 --> 00:06:54,970
Well, this just got interesting!

100
00:06:57,450 --> 00:07:00,120
This bucking bronco is mine!

101
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:02,230
Oh? Look at him go.

102
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:05,570
Thanks for equipping them with SE plugs!

103
00:07:05,570 --> 00:07:07,190
The SE Plug:

104
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:13,950
In this world, there are many vehicles 
which use magical power as energy.

105
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:21,050
Among them, the magic four-wheelers and 
magic motorcycles are equipped with SE Plugs

106
00:07:21,050 --> 00:07:26,270
in order to send magic power from the 
driver directly to the internal engine.

107
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:30,680
It's definitely tough to make sure I don't 
lose all my magic power with these things.

108
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,300
I don't got a choice.

109
00:07:32,470 --> 00:07:34,620
Here I go!

110
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,950
Sounds like fun!

111
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:38,260
You're challenging me to a race?

112
00:07:38,670 --> 00:07:41,520
There ain't no rules, so 
you'd better be prepared!

113
00:07:52,730 --> 00:07:56,950
You've got some nice style for being a 
goody-two-shoes from an official guild!

114
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:59,700
Don't underestimate Fairy Tail!

115
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:01,910
Ice Make Lance!

116
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:07,660
You're still too slow!

117
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:09,950
Damn it, it's hard to aim!

118
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,050
Do you really have the speed to pass me?

119
00:08:17,220 --> 00:08:18,800
High Side Rush!

120
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:20,010
Tires?

121
00:08:22,350 --> 00:08:24,080
Not bad.

122
00:08:24,350 --> 00:08:29,380
But the Dead Grand Prix 
has just gotten started!

123
00:08:30,230 --> 00:08:32,630
There! Try getting past this!

124
00:08:39,910 --> 00:08:43,330
Damn it, this is nuts!

125
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:45,830
What's the matter, hot stuff?

126
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:59,220
I can't lose! For Erza!

127
00:08:59,970 --> 00:09:02,170
I wonder what the explosion was just now?

128
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:03,800
A newcomer?

129
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,270
No...

130
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,670
Lyon-sama, that's...

131
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:09,060
Oracion Seis!

132
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:10,850
Lyon!

133
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:11,730
Gray!

134
00:09:12,130 --> 00:09:14,740
Perfect timing! Get on!

135
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:15,820
What?

136
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,740
Just get on already!

137
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,540
Lyon-sama?

138
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:24,710
Don't worry! Stay here on standby!

139
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,960
Standby?

140
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,990
What other choice do I have?

141
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:40,200
Gray, where's Wendy?

142
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,020
Don't worry. Natsu saved her.

143
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:45,100
I see. Impressive.

144
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:50,650
Anyway, can you get him? I can't use 
magic well while I'm drivin' this thing.

145
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,900
Well, you just watch real carefully.

146
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:56,970
I'll show you how creation magic is done!

147
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:58,240
Put your money where your mouth is!

148
00:09:58,860 --> 00:09:59,950
Here I go.

149
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,200
Pitiful.

150
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:06,640
You still use both hands 
when you use creation magic?

151
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:10,850
Lyon... You're using two hands?

152
00:10:12,950 --> 00:10:14,660
It's how Ul taught us, right?

153
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:19,130
Ice Make...

154
00:10:20,050 --> 00:10:21,630
Eagle!

155
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:24,920
You get him?

156
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:27,140
No... There's no reaction.

157
00:10:27,590 --> 00:10:29,230
Enough playing around.

158
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:32,960
Ice Make...

159
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:32,970
Ice Make...

160
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:34,150
Ape!

161
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,160
Hammer!

162
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:39,900
That's some speedy creation 
magic you have there.

163
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:42,070
Fast is good!

164
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:43,700
But you're not there yet!

165
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:49,220
You just can't catch up to my speed.

166
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,750
I can't hit him!

167
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:55,960
Calm yourself, Gray! He's at 4 o'clock!

168
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,440
If you concentrate, you can follow anyone!

169
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,160
Concentrate, huh?

170
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:02,740
Okay then...

171
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:04,800
Let's do this, Lyon!

172
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,670
Fire on my mark, and don't hold back!

173
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:10,810
Why did they strip? And damn, that was fast.

174
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:13,540
Why did he take off his clothes?

175
00:11:13,540 --> 00:11:15,570
Is that also...love?

176
00:11:25,450 --> 00:11:28,330
Now! 50 meters in front!

177
00:11:28,330 --> 00:11:29,620
I see you!

178
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:35,050
Ice Geyser!

179
00:11:35,050 --> 00:11:36,840
Snow Dragon!

180
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:39,410
Damn it!

181
00:11:39,410 --> 00:11:41,300
He's sped up even faster!

182
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:44,300
What's the matter? I'm over here!

183
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:58,460
You'll never hit me with those 
attacks. Not in your entire life...

184
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:01,490
No one can keep up with my speed.

185
00:12:02,130 --> 00:12:05,490
He's strong... Is this what 
Oracion Seis really is?

186
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:10,270
Now, I need to get around 
to finishing you off,

187
00:12:10,270 --> 00:12:12,460
and bringing back that girl.

188
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:15,130
Lend me your ear, Gray.

189
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:19,350
I've found his weakness.

190
00:12:32,340 --> 00:12:34,230
The results of the investigation are in.

191
00:12:34,770 --> 00:12:36,640
About Oracion Seis?

192
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:43,140
It's possible that Brain was once 
part of the Bureau of Magic.

193
00:12:43,140 --> 00:12:46,420
The Bureau of Magic? Then, 
what's his true identity?

194
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:48,370
That's still under investigation.

195
00:12:48,940 --> 00:12:54,880
What worries me is the R-system, in 
other words, the Tower of Heaven.

196
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:57,040
This seems to have something to do with it.

197
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,970
I've got reports indicating that.

198
00:12:59,970 --> 00:13:02,630
There's a connection to Jellal...

199
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:04,320
That's what you mean, right?

200
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,590
Yes.

201
00:13:05,590 --> 00:13:08,190
But I don't know...

202
00:13:12,870 --> 00:13:17,560
What's Brain trying to accomplish with magic?

203
00:13:18,430 --> 00:13:20,050
It'll be okay.

204
00:13:21,730 --> 00:13:23,900
Natsu and the others are on the scene.

205
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:27,360
So, I'm sure things will be fine.

206
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:32,250
I suppose so.

207
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,490
It would be nice if they don't destroy 
things any more than necessary, though...

208
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:39,480
<i>That's</i> what you're worried about?

209
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:45,390
Lyon-sama... What could he be talking about?

210
00:13:48,490 --> 00:13:51,760
Having a strategy session? How pointless.

211
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,030
Understand?

212
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,170
What?!

213
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:57,850
Just like I said.

214
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:01,900
You are no longer needed!

215
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:04,010
Hey, Lyon!

216
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:05,440
Damn you!

217
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,720
Lyon-sama, what are you doing?

218
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:11,320
God damn it! Let me go, Lyon!

219
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,660
Don't give me this crap!

220
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:17,030
Just stay up there and watch, Gray!

221
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:20,510
Turning on your friend? That's harsh, man...

222
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:23,230
Please, don't get me wrong.

223
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:25,770
He's not my friend.

224
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:28,610
We just happened to have the same teacher.

225
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:30,180
That's all.

226
00:14:30,180 --> 00:14:30,890
Why, you...

227
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:33,240
But Lyon-sama...

228
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,450
No complaining!

229
00:14:34,930 --> 00:14:37,750
Lamia Scale will be bagging this one!

230
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:39,830
Let's go, Sherry!

231
00:14:39,830 --> 00:14:41,400
Uh, sure.

232
00:14:41,950 --> 00:14:47,280
That overconfidence isn't 
going to help your chances.

233
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:51,620
Well, your chances were zero 
to begin with anyway...

234
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:53,400
Yap-yap-yap, little doggy!

235
00:14:54,370 --> 00:14:57,500
Doll Attack, Rock Doll!

236
00:14:59,630 --> 00:15:02,710
Nice power, but it lacks speed!

237
00:15:03,290 --> 00:15:04,940
Slow, slow!

238
00:15:05,550 --> 00:15:06,920
I can't see!

239
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:10,130
In that case... Wood Doll!

240
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:14,850
You can't catch me with magic like that!

241
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:16,850
Then how about this, I wonder?

242
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,910
Oh, crap!

243
00:15:18,910 --> 00:15:20,210
...Psych.

244
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,560
He slipped out?

245
00:15:23,410 --> 00:15:24,630
You're slow!

246
00:15:28,620 --> 00:15:30,400
What are you, slow in the head?

247
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,380
Oh, that's rich.

248
00:15:34,380 --> 00:15:36,280
You're the one that's slow in the head!

249
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,620
Your weak point is the 
weakness of your attacks!

250
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:44,000
No matter how fast you are, 
you can't seal the deal!

251
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:48,460
Ice Make Hedgehog!

252
00:15:49,530 --> 00:15:52,010
Close in on me, and you're shish kebab...

253
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:53,970
So what'll you do?

254
00:15:54,690 --> 00:15:57,400
Come at me with that 
speed you're so proud of!

255
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,060
Such a fool you are...

256
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:02,180
Gear Change... Red Zone!

257
00:16:08,230 --> 00:16:10,570
Now <i>that</i> was my top speed.

258
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:14,370
You think I'd be serious at first 
against weaker opponents like you?

259
00:16:14,370 --> 00:16:15,290
Really?

260
00:16:15,650 --> 00:16:16,950
I'm not done yet!

261
00:16:16,950 --> 00:16:18,240
Hey now...

262
00:16:18,730 --> 00:16:20,370
Where do you think you're going?

263
00:16:25,580 --> 00:16:26,750
Lyon-sama...

264
00:16:32,010 --> 00:16:34,290
What happened to that 
momentum you had at first?

265
00:16:40,410 --> 00:16:42,220
Well, you are damn tenacious...

266
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:45,110
How far is he going?

267
00:16:52,570 --> 00:16:55,150
Ice Make Eagle!

268
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:59,160
Don't you understand that you can't hit me?

269
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:05,370
Hey, what's wrong? You think 
you can stop me with that, huh?

270
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:11,520
You said that I don't have any 
way to seal the deal with you.

271
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:14,960
Well, since you asked...

272
00:17:17,820 --> 00:17:20,030
This should do nicely.

273
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:28,270
As long as I have the speed, I can get you 
first, before you have a chance to use magic.

274
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:33,230
Well, there's nothing wrong with being 
a bit arrogant when you're young.

275
00:17:33,230 --> 00:17:35,170
But you were up against the wrong dude.

276
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,150
I'm one of Oracion Seis.

277
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:43,700
Six Generals. Six Prayers.

278
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,660
Six Pillars that will never crumble.

279
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:52,520
Only death awaits those who rock the pillars.

280
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,290
As I thought.

281
00:17:55,800 --> 00:18:03,600
When I saw the birds flying by so fast in the 
sky, I figured out how your magic really works.

282
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:12,900
Your magic doesn't increase your own speed.

283
00:18:13,210 --> 00:18:15,680
It lowers the speed of your opponents...

284
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:20,040
Or more accurately, it slows down
their sense of time in a certain area.

285
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:24,350
In other words, you slow <i>me</i> down.

286
00:18:25,510 --> 00:18:30,650
And since the magic only 
affects a certain area,

287
00:18:30,650 --> 00:18:33,400
when someone sees you from 
outside your range...

288
00:18:37,540 --> 00:18:40,090
They can take away your speed!

289
00:18:45,130 --> 00:18:48,310
That's why you had me get 
so far away from him?

290
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:52,270
I see... I see it all!

291
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:56,550
But at that range... 
There's no way he'll hit!

292
00:18:57,110 --> 00:18:58,110
Oh, he'll hit.

293
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,350
It doesn't matter how far away he is!

294
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:05,260
'Cause there's nothing stronger
than a member of Fairy Tail

295
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:07,290
and the strength of their passion!!

296
00:19:07,630 --> 00:19:11,210
Super Freeze Arrow!

297
00:19:16,550 --> 00:19:18,090
It's fast!

298
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,000
My prayer...

299
00:19:26,450 --> 00:19:33,850
To be faster than anyone... To be faster...

300
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,820
You did it, Lyon.

301
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:54,150
We still got five more of these guys.

302
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:59,150
I actually thought you two 
were fighting back there!

303
00:19:59,150 --> 00:20:02,220
I'd expect nothing less from the older pupil.

304
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:06,200
Can you stand?

305
00:20:06,540 --> 00:20:08,020
Don't make fun of me.

306
00:20:10,170 --> 00:20:12,600
It's not over!

307
00:20:13,510 --> 00:20:19,250
I swear on the name Oracion Seis, if I 
go down in defeat, I'll take you with me!

308
00:20:21,820 --> 00:20:23,070
That's...

309
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:25,070
An explosive lacrima...

310
00:20:25,070 --> 00:20:27,120
You bastard... Are you planning on...

311
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,280
One man, one kill!

312
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,500
Why, you...

313
00:20:32,060 --> 00:20:36,010
Crap... Why do I have to run
out of magic power now?

314
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:39,290
Lyon!

315
00:20:39,290 --> 00:20:40,420
Lyon-sama!

316
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:54,890
Sheesh...

317
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:58,280
The things I do for you, younger pupil...

318
00:21:13,330 --> 00:21:16,520
Lyon!

319
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:20,350
Lyon-sama!

320
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:26,820
Lyon!

321
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:43,890
Racer is... gone?

322
00:21:44,410 --> 00:21:48,280
One corner of the Six Generals has broken?

323
00:21:50,130 --> 00:21:53,190
I underestimated our enemy!

324
00:21:55,530 --> 00:21:58,360
I never thought I would 
have to wake him up...

325
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:00,970
Midnight!

326
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:08,110
Awake?

327
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,150
Get rid of every last one of them.

328
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:19,500
Yes... Father.

329
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:59,800
I sure wish I could breathe fire...

330
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,040
What's this all of a sudden?

331
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:05,610
'Cause I could fry fish, or light 
up dark places... It's handy!

332
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:07,870
Then why don't you try eating my flames?

333
00:24:07,870 --> 00:24:10,450
It might let you use breath attacks!

334
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:13,510
Cats aren't good with hot food, so I'll pass.

335
00:24:13,980 --> 00:24:16,080
Next time: Darkness.

336
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:18,110
Just try eating it, sheesh!

337
00:24:18,110 --> 00:24:20,060
There's at least a chance, right?

338
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:22,340
I guess you're right. Let's see here...

339
00:24:22,340 --> 00:24:22,580
Here.

340
00:24:22,580 --> 00:24:24,600


